  <prompt>
    Author `FileManifestExtractor` (NEW) — deterministic regex/heuristic-based extractor for `{ sections[], tables[], pageCount, language }` from uploaded file text content per architecture §4.4 + §6.1. NO LLM call (50ms budget per architecture §6.1). Pure C# heuristics: detect section headings (`^\d+\.\s+\w` / `^[A-Z][A-Z ]{4,}` / `^Section \d`), detect tables (rows of pipe-delimited / tab-delimited text), count pages from form-feed `\f` characters (PDF.js extraction convention) OR fallback to estimated `chars / 3000`, detect language via existing detector if present (`Microsoft.Recognizers.Text` or simple heuristics — skip if unavailable, return "en").
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in deterministic text-processing extraction.</role>

  <goal>
    `FileManifestExtractor.cs` exists with `IFileManifestExtractor` interface + `ExtractAsync(string textContent, string fileName, string contentType, CancellationToken ct) → FileManifest`. Result shape per architecture §6.1: `{ Sections: List&lt;SectionInfo&gt;, Tables: List&lt;TableInfo&gt;, PageCount: int, Language: string, ExtractedChars: int, ExtractedTokens: int }`. Stateless service. Target ≤50ms for a 50-page document.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §4.4 + §6.1. Third parallel enrichment service (alongside 067 classification + 068 summarization). Pure deterministic — no LLM cost. Output feeds `get_file_manifest` tool (task 084) and the layered context card (076). PDF text content arriving from frontend (per architecture §6.1 client-side text extraction) typically has form-feed `\f` page delimiters from PDF.js; use these for pageCount.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Chat/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Concrete-class injection — no `IServiceProvider`. Constructor minimal: probably just `ILogger`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Service lives in `Services/Ai/Sessions/` — within AI module.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tier-1 logging: fileId, sessionId, durationMs, section count, table count, pageCount. NEVER textContent or section heading content.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task publish size measurement. NO new NuGet dependency unless absolutely necessary (e.g., language detection should fall back to "en" rather than adding a package).</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture §6.1">Target latency ~50ms — heuristic-only, no LLM call.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No new external API. No Azure Document Intelligence. Pure C# heuristics only.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-029-bff-publish-hygiene.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read peer services in `Services/Ai/Sessions/` for style.</step>
    <step order="2">Define `IFileManifestExtractor` + `FileManifest` record + sub-records (`SectionInfo { string Name, int StartCharOffset, int EndCharOffset, int? StartPage, int? EndPage }`, `TableInfo { string Name, int StartCharOffset, int? Page }`).</step>
    <step order="3">Implement extractor:
      - Section detection regex: `^\d+\.\s+[A-Z]`, `^[A-Z][A-Z ]{4,}$`, `^Section \d+`, `^Article [IVX]+`
      - Table detection: 3+ consecutive lines with `|` or tab delimiters; or markdown-table headers
      - PageCount: count `\f` characters; fallback `Math.Max(1, textContent.Length / 3000)`
      - Language: simple heuristic ("if mostly ASCII letters → 'en'"); future-extensible
      - ExtractedTokens: estimate `chars / 4` (rough)</step>
    <step order="4">Author unit test stub in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Sessions/FileManifestExtractorTests.cs` — fixture with synthetic text covering all heuristics.</step>
    <step order="5">Performance test: benchmark on synthetic 50-page document; assert &lt;100ms.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`.</step>
    <step order="7">Measure BFF publish size.</step>
    <step order="8">code-review + adr-check.</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 069 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Peer services + Models/Chat</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Extractor + interface + records + tests</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">dotnet build / test / publish + benchmark</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/FileManifestExtractor.cs (NEW)</output>
