  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`FileManifestExtractor.cs` exists, stateless, no LLM call.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Returns `FileManifest` per architecture §6.1 shape.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Performance test exits &lt;100ms on synthetic 50-page input.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No log statement carries textContent or section heading content.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` + tests exit 0.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish delta &lt;0.3 MB (no LLM client overhead).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">code-review + adr-check exit 0.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Language detection is intentionally simple — defer Microsoft.Recognizers.Text or similar to a follow-up if real localization needs emerge. Per CLAUDE.md "No new external API surface" — keep dependencies minimal.
  </notes>

